  <name>Kuro</name>

  <!-- Translators: the brief summary of the application as it appears in a software center. -->
  <summary>Master the art of deduction in this modern logic puzzle game</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Kuro is a modern, native GTK4 implementation of the classic Hitori logic puzzle.
      The goal is to eliminate duplicate numbers in each row and column by painting them out,
      following three simple rules:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>No number can appear more than once in a row or column (unpainted).</li>
      <li>Painted cells cannot touch horizontally or vertically.</li>
      <li>All unpainted cells must be connected in a single group.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Rebuilt for the modern GNOME desktop, Kuro features a beautiful, adaptive user interface
      that looks great on any device. Whether you're a puzzle veteran or a newcomer,
      Kuro offers a relaxing yet challenging experience with multiple board sizes and
      helper tools to guide your way.
    </p>
  </description>
